 {td}**9.**{/td}
 {td}**{jira:GMS-9}**{/td}
 {td}**Cybersecurity**{/td}
 {td}Review TLS/certificate authentication, RBAC, audit logging, and offline authentication requirements; verify account management is included in Operator role per review R7{/td}
 {td}Vremere Adrian{/td}
 {td}2026-04-25{/td}
 {/tr}
 {tr}
 {td}**9.1**{/td}
 {td}{jira:GMS-87|showSummary=false}{/td}
 {td}All communication between the GMS edge controller and the cloud server SHALL be encrypted using TLS 1.2 or higher, and the edge controller SHALL authenticate to the cloud broker using X.509 client certificates before any sensor data or actuator command is transmitted or received.{/td}
 {td}Run network traffic inspection; confirm all cloud-bound traffic is TLS-encrypted; verify broker rejects connection without valid client certificate; move GMS-87 to Project Accepted{/td}
 {td}Vremere Adrian{/td}
 {td}2026-04-30{/td}
 {/tr}
 {tr}
 {td}**9.2**{/td}
 {td}{jira:GMS-88|showSummary=false}{/td}
 {td}The GMS web dashboard SHALL implement role-based access control with a minimum of two roles — Operator (full read/write access to controls, configuration, and user account management) and Viewer (read-only access to sensor data and alerts) — with role assignments persisted per user account. An account holding the Operator role SHALL be able to create, modify, and deactivate other user accounts and assign the Viewer role to them. The initial Operator account shall be provisioned at installation. (Account management added to Operator role per review R7.){/td}
 {td}Verify Viewer cannot activate actuators or modify thresholds (expect permission error); verify Operator can create and assign a Viewer account; update GMS-88 text; move to Project Accepted{/td}
 {td}Vremere Adrian{/td}
 {td}2026-04-30{/td}
 {/tr}
 {tr}
 {td}**9.3**{/td}
 {td}{jira:GMS-89|showSummary=false}{/td}
 {td}WHEN an unauthenticated or unauthorised request is made to any GMS API endpoint or dashboard route, the system SHALL reject the request with an HTTP 401 or 403 response and log the attempt with a timestamp and source IP address.{/td}
 {td}Submit requests with invalid token and with valid Viewer token to Operator-only endpoints; verify HTTP 401 and 403 responses respectively; confirm audit log entry with timestamp and source IP; move GMS-89 to Project Accepted{/td}
 {td}Vremere Adrian{/td}
 {td}2026-05-02{/td}
 {/tr}
 {tr}
 {td}**9.4**{/td}
 {td}{jira:GMS-90|showSummary=false}{/td}
 {td}WHILE the edge controller is operating in offline autonomous mode, the system SHALL continue to enforce local authentication for any direct API access to the controller, rejecting requests that do not present a valid pre-provisioned credential.{/td}
 {td}Simulate cloud outage; send direct HTTP request to edge controller API without credentials; verify HTTP 401 response; move GMS-90 to Project Accepted{/td}
 {td}Vremere Adrian{/td}
 {td}2026-05-05{/td}
 {/tr}
 {/table}
